OL,4,Cleft mum in the dark about daughter's
OL,5,Ccare
OL,7,F"I again I said straight away 'I'm so
OL,8,Fsorry, the consent for her to go into
OL,9,Ftheatre, you're not having it, because
OL,10,Fbefore my daughter goes in I want full
OL,11,Faccess to all the information, and
OL,12,Ftherefore it's imperative that I have
OL,13,Fan interpreter'. And they were just so
OL,14,Fcondescending and made me feel like a
OL,15,Fbad mother.
OL,17,F"I was actually trying to say
OL,18,F'actually no, the problem is with you,
OL,19,Fat this point this is your
OL,20,Fresponsibility to make sure you can
OL,21,Fgive me all the information involved'."
